# KFC-Style Herb Blend

A white-pepper-forward, Southern-inspired herb-and-spice mix adapted for air-fried applications and perfect for pita-crisp crusts. Balanced, aromatic, and ideal for thin, crisp coatings without added oil.

## Ingredients  
*(Makes one seasoning batch for 2 cups crushed pita crisps)*

- 1 tbsp all-purpose flour  
- 1 tsp white pepper  
- ½ tsp black pepper  
- 1 tsp paprika (sweet)  
- 1 tsp garlic powder  
- ½ tsp celery seed, lightly crushed  
- 1 tsp dried thyme  
- 1 tsp dried oregano  
- ½ tsp dried basil  
- ¼–½ tsp dried sage  
- ½ tsp ground ginger  
- ¼ tsp mustard powder (optional)  
- ½ tsp fine salt, **adjust based on pita crisp baseline saltiness**

## Method

1. Combine all ingredients in a bowl.  
2. Lightly crush celery seed before adding.  
3. Mix thoroughly until uniform.  
4. Store airtight up to 3 months.

## Usage Notes

- One full batch seasons **2 cups finely crushed pita crisps**.  
- Perfect for air-fryer chicken, turkey cutlets, pork, and roasted vegetables.  
- Increase white pepper by +¼ tsp for a more classic fried-chicken bite.

